name: Luh tyler

name: Aya Nakamura

name: Roedel

name: Luie Louis
bio_summary: Luie Louis is a rapper/producer from Antwerp. In 2017, he put himself on the map of the Flemish hip-hop landscape with his debut album 'LoveLifeLouis'. With the record with features from NAG, Zwangere Guy, Blu Samu, among others, he toured the country and flattened many halls. Around this period he also started a band on 'De Luie Live band' (something that was unique at the moment in the Flemish scene) released a record called 'The golden Classics' and toured with it.

name: Blu Samu

name: Marteria

name: Keak Da Sneak

name: Rich the factor

name: Pries

name: Moss

In 2013 he was murdered by a member of the far-right political party Golden Dawn.

name: MC Daleste

name: Bad New Brown

name: Lele

name: Dolla

name: VL Mike

name: Half a Mill

name: Camoflauge

name: Sabotage

name: Jam Master Jay

name: Dj Uncle Al
bio_summary: Albert Moss (August 14, 1969 %u2013 September 10, 2001), better known by the stage name "DJ Uncle Al," was an American DJ based in Miami, Florida. Moss was known for his trend setting and innovative abilities in music producing and broadcasting as well as his philosophy of "peace in the hood" and non-violence in the community. He was shot and killed on September 10, 2001.

name: Bugz
bio_summary: Bugz was an american rapper from Detroit, Michigan. He was one of the members of the D12 group. He was murdered in 1999.

name: Freaky Tah

name: Yaki Kadafi

name: Stretch

name: Charizma

He is best known for his work with Peanut Butter Wolf; the two artists formed a duo after meeting in 1990 but their musical partnership was cut short following Charizma's murder in 1993.

name: D Boy

name: Paul C

name: Scott La Rock

name: Clipse
bio_summary: Clipse is an American hip hop duo, formed by brothers Gene "No Malice" Thornton and Terrence "Pusha T" Thornton, in Virginia Beach, Virginia, in 1992. The group was affiliated with the production team The Neptune.

name: Petey Pablo

name: People Under The Stairs

name: Raz Simone

name: Soulking

He incorporates reggae, soul, hip hop and Algerian raï in his music.

name: Kojey Radical

name: Toot
bio_summary: Toot is an american rapper from Omaha, Nebraska.

name: XV

name: Dayton Family

name: Death Grips

name: Battlecat

name: Sister Fa

name: Lemdi & Moax

name: Bastos

name: O'Rosko Raricim

name: Mystik

name: Lil Kim

name: Ciara

name: Sameer Ahmad
bio_summary: Sameer Ahmad is a french rapper from Flers.

name: Tierra Whack

He was best known as a member of the pioneering Texas hip hop group Geto Boys, a group he originally joined as a dancer in 1986 as Little Billy.

name: 42 Dugg

name: Soso Maness
bio_summary: Soso Maness is a french Rapper from Font Vert, Marseille.

name: Icewear Vezzo

name: Peezy

name: Babyface Ray

name: Tyga

name: DaBaby

name: Sada baby

name: Da Brat

name: Noname

name: Cellyru

name: Kilo G

name: Lil Blood

name: J Stallin

name: Chingy

name: Crime Mob

name: Krilino

name: OG Boo Dirty

Although his first single was released under the name MC EZ in 1988, he is best known for his 1994 hit single "Flava In Ya Ear", which was released under his real name.

name: Dead Prez
bio_summary: Dead Prez, is a hip hop duo from the United States, composed of stic.man and M-1, formed in 1996 in New York City. They are known for their confrontational style, combined with socialist lyrics focused on both militant social justice, Marxism, and Pan-Africanism. The duo maintains an ethical stance against corporate control over the media, especially hip hop record labels.

name: Enima

name: Afrika Bambaataa
